  <!-- WHAT WE DO -->
  <p class="lead p-5 ">
    Raksha is a Not for Profit - Non Government Organization that
    aims to provide shelter to destitute, abandoned, underprivileged ,
    disabled, mentally week Children & Women and Senior Citizens of our
    society, regardless of their religion, caste or social status. Raksha
    will focus on the basic needs of these individuals and provide
    education, healthcare and vocational skills necessary to transform them
    into responsible citizens of our society. We believe that each child,
    woman and senior citizen in our nation has the right to a better quality
    of life & our objective is to help them to achieve it. It chooses to do
    this by establishing, maintaining, supporting and running centres at
    various places and provide shelter and rehabilitation to those members of
    our society who need it the most. Raksha is established to help
    downtrodden individuals claw their way into a position where they can
    support themselves & contribute significantly to the society. Each life we
    save & improve will be an inspiration for others and will end up saving
    multiple other lives. Raksha envisages a world in which each
    individual is Empowered enough to not only take care of himself but also
    others who need support around him.
  </p>
